I'm saying that he's gone to these
great lengths to hide his past.

719
00:59:06,209 --> 00:59:10,043
I'm saying that he was in St. Louis
when the federal building was bombed.

720
00:59:10,113 --> 00:59:13,981
And I'm saying that there is
a blueprint in his house...

721
00:59:14,050 --> 00:59:16,484
that he does not want me to see!

722
00:59:20,657 --> 00:59:23,319
- Are you <i>listening</i> to yourself?
- Are you listening to me?

723
00:59:23,393 --> 00:59:25,452
- Your neighbor?
- Yes!

724
00:59:25,528 --> 00:59:27,996
Is a terrorist?

725
00:59:28,064 --> 00:59:30,362
He's been blowing up buildings?

726
00:59:30,433 --> 00:59:34,961
There's something going on over there.
Something is being planned.

727
00:59:35,038 --> 00:59:37,563
Something's being planned?
Yeah, and in his spare time...

728
00:59:37,640 --> 00:59:41,235
hey pays the mortgage
and takes his kid to camp.

729
00:59:41,311 --> 00:59:45,805
- That house is not normal.
- That house is normal!

730
00:59:45,882 --> 00:59:48,350
Remember when we were over there
the other night?

731
00:59:48,418 --> 00:59:50,978
- Him discussing politics?
- Yeah, we disagree about politics.

732
00:59:51,054 --> 00:59:54,217
And Washington?
And Leah?

733
00:59:54,290 --> 00:59:56,258
- Do you remember this?
- Oh, my...

734
00:59:56,326 --> 00:59:58,658
The guy is testing me.

735
00:59:58,728 --> 01:00:02,095
He wants to see
if I'm an enemy or an ally.

736
01:00:03,199 --> 01:00:06,657
You are the one who brought up Leah.

737
01:00:06,736 --> 01:00:09,637
Is that what this is about?

738
01:00:09,706 --> 01:00:12,174
No, it's not about Leah!

739
01:00:16,079 --> 01:00:18,479
You know, this class...

740
01:00:18,548 --> 01:00:21,210
that you slave over...

741
01:00:21,284 --> 01:00:26,119
to carry on Leah's work,
to have <i>something</i> in her memory?

742
01:00:29,659 --> 01:00:33,322
You know,
plots and conspiracies...

743
01:00:33,396 --> 01:00:35,990
and red flags going up.

744
01:00:36,065 --> 01:00:39,091
Yeah, this is Leah's world now.

745
01:00:41,170 --> 01:00:42,762
I'm...

746
01:00:50,046 --> 01:00:51,638
I can't.

747
01:00:54,584 --> 01:00:57,018
Listen, I <i>know....</i>

748
01:00:57,086 --> 01:01:00,613
that he's changed his name...

749
01:01:00,690 --> 01:01:03,318
- Stop it, for me.
- He lived in St Louis...

750
01:01:03,393 --> 01:01:06,191
when the bombs were goin' off.

751
01:01:06,262 --> 01:01:09,698
He's working on this building
that he doesn't want me to see.

752
01:01:14,137 --> 01:01:16,071
I don't think
I can stay here tonight.

753
01:01:17,707 --> 01:01:20,232
I'm not staying.

754
01:02:34,217 --> 01:02:36,447
Never did like that picture.

755
01:02:39,288 --> 01:02:41,222
You know me, Michael?

756
01:02:42,291 --> 01:02:44,259
You think you know me?

757
01:02:45,862 --> 01:02:48,831
Yeah, you know me better
than I know myself, don't you?

758
01:02:49,832 --> 01:02:52,300
<i>Kansas City Star.</i>
I saw you.

759
01:02:52,368 --> 01:02:54,996
You wanna tell me something
I don't know?

760
01:02:56,472 --> 01:02:59,908
- I know what I read.
- You know a 16-year-old kid.

761
01:03:02,011 --> 01:03:04,036
You don't know me.

762
01:03:04,113 --> 01:03:06,274
You know a kid at 16.

763
01:03:09,519 --> 01:03:11,987
Damn you!
You've been a guest in my house!

764
01:03:12,054 --> 01:03:14,852
You're a guest in mine, Fenimore.

765
01:03:15,958 --> 01:03:18,688
Bill, Will, William...
What do I call you?

766
01:03:18,761 --> 01:03:22,788
Who the hell do you think you are
judging me? What gives you the right?

767
01:03:26,135 --> 01:03:28,103
You ever worked on a farm?

768
01:03:33,176 --> 01:03:35,770
Make your living,
support your family?

769
01:03:37,280 --> 01:03:43,150
The government stole my father's water...
a stream running through our land.

770
01:03:43,219 --> 01:03:45,813
Said they were appropriating it
for other uses.

771
01:03:47,423 --> 01:03:51,519
We couldn't grow crops,
we couldn't raise cattle.

772
01:03:51,594 --> 01:03:54,028
We had loans we couldn't pay.

773
01:03:55,965 --> 01:03:57,899
My father woke up one mornin'...

774
01:03:57,967 --> 01:04:01,459
and he realized
he was worth more dead than alive.

775
01:04:03,005 --> 01:04:05,667
His skin and bones...

776
01:04:05,741 --> 01:04:08,539
were worth more
in insurance money...

777
01:04:08,611 --> 01:04:10,909
than as a damn farmer.

778
01:04:13,716 --> 01:04:16,651
I found his tractor...

779
01:04:16,719 --> 01:04:19,688
at the bottom of the bluffs
behind our house.

780
01:04:19,755 --> 01:04:21,689
He made it look like an accident.

781
01:04:21,757 --> 01:04:26,717
I found his body.
And the note?

782
01:04:28,965 --> 01:04:30,956
He wrote it to me.

783
01:04:37,006 --> 01:04:39,770
Insurance money paid off
what Mom could...

784
01:04:39,842 --> 01:04:42,436
but it wasn't enough.

785
01:04:43,512 --> 01:04:47,676
Neighbors...
Neighbors took our land at auction.

786
01:04:49,252 --> 01:04:52,915
All because some bureaucrat
stuck a pin in a map...

787
01:04:54,624 --> 01:04:58,424
in some creek in the middle of Kansas,
said we couldn't use our own water.

788
01:04:58,494 --> 01:05:00,428
Doesn't give you the right
to build a bomb.

789
01:05:00,496 --> 01:05:04,159
I was sixteen.
Sixteen!

790
01:05:04,233 --> 01:05:07,327
You ever do anything wrong
when you were 16?

791
01:05:08,571 --> 01:05:10,903
You ever crash your car?

792
01:05:10,973 --> 01:05:15,672
You ever, uh, steal anything?
You ever screw the wrong girl?

793
01:05:15,745 --> 01:05:18,407
You gonna tell your kid everything
you did when you were 16?

794
01:05:18,481 --> 01:05:21,143
The lies you told?
The drugs you took?

795
01:05:23,119 --> 01:05:25,053
I've been judged for this!

796
01:05:25,121 --> 01:05:29,785
I got sent away for it, and it was
the best thing that ever happened to me.

797
01:05:29,859 --> 01:05:31,793
The best thing.

798
01:05:38,567 --> 01:05:40,159
Who's Oliver?

799
01:05:48,377 --> 01:05:50,709
He was my best friend growin' up.

800
01:05:53,883 --> 01:05:56,613
He died when we were both 25.

801
01:05:59,121 --> 01:06:01,055
I did it to honor him...

802
01:06:03,292 --> 01:06:05,226
to carry on his name.

803
01:06:07,229 --> 01:06:09,163
And to hide.

804
01:06:10,633 --> 01:06:12,567
Yeah, to hide.

805
01:06:14,170 --> 01:06:17,697
I didn't want any son I had
knowing what I did.

806
01:06:19,909 --> 01:06:23,470
I didn't want my kids
to be burdened...

807
01:06:23,546 --> 01:06:26,606
with people looking through
old newspapers.

808
01:06:28,951 --> 01:06:31,613
I'm not proud of this.

809
01:06:33,923 --> 01:06:35,948
This isn't pride.

810
01:06:38,361 --> 01:06:40,989
I wish it never happened.

811
01:06:42,898 --> 01:06:46,459
You know, I wish to <i>God....</i>

812
01:06:46,535 --> 01:06:49,265
that my family could have...

813
01:06:49,338 --> 01:06:52,000
my father's good name.

814
01:06:57,613 --> 01:07:00,741
You know, you have a right
to know who lives next door...

815
01:07:00,816 --> 01:07:05,549
who talks to your kid,
who considers himself your friend.

816
01:07:07,189 --> 01:07:09,885
But you also have the right...

817
01:07:09,959 --> 01:07:13,019
If you have a problem with me,
if you have issues with <i>me....</i>

818
01:07:14,897 --> 01:07:18,333
you could have the decency
to walk across the street...

819
01:07:18,401 --> 01:07:21,063
and tell me to my face.

820
01:11:29,752 --> 01:11:32,516
<i>Hi, this is Michael.</i>
<i>Leave a message.</i>

821
01:11:32,588 --> 01:11:34,886
It's me. Listen.

822
01:11:34,957 --> 01:11:38,256
I think you're right.
I saw <i>Oliver....</i>

823
01:11:38,327 --> 01:11:41,956
at the mall in the garage.

824
01:11:42,031 --> 01:11:45,762
He switched cars with somebody,
and I followed him...

825
01:11:45,834 --> 01:11:48,098
to this warehouse delivery place.

826
01:11:50,339 --> 01:11:54,639
They were unloading
these long, metal boxes.

827
01:11:56,679 --> 01:12:01,116
I want to talk to you.
I'm coming over, okay?

828
01:12:09,525 --> 01:12:11,220
I knew it was you.

829
01:12:17,366 --> 01:12:19,300
What are you doing here?

830
01:12:22,571 --> 01:12:26,564
Just shopping.
What are you doing here?

831
01:12:28,644 --> 01:12:30,236
Shopping.

832
01:12:33,682 --> 01:12:35,479
Great.

833
01:12:35,551 --> 01:12:37,143
Yeah.

834
01:12:56,538 --> 01:13:00,338
<i>They say a man was shot several times</i>
<i>while driving along 19th street.</i>

835
01:13:00,409 --> 01:13:04,140
<i>The car struck several other vehicles</i>
<i>before slamming into a tree.</i>

836
01:13:04,213 --> 01:13:07,341
<i>The victim was pronounced</i>
<i>dead at the scene.</i>

837
01:13:07,416 --> 01:13:09,577
<i>Elsewhere, a single-car accident</i>
<i>near Reston is tying up....</i>

838
01:13:09,651 --> 01:13:12,711
<i>evening traffic on westbound</i>
<i>Route</i> 7 <i>at this hour.</i>

839
01:13:12,788 --> 01:13:15,518
<i>Details are sketchy at this point.</i>
<i>What we can tell you...</i>

840
01:13:15,591 --> 01:13:17,821
<i>from our overhead shot is that</i>
<i>the accident took place....</i>

841
01:13:17,893 --> 01:13:20,088
<i>near the Pine Glenn Outlet Center.</i>

842
01:13:20,162 --> 01:13:22,460
<i>No other vehicles appear to be</i>
<i>involved in what police say...</i>

843
01:13:22,531 --> 01:13:24,123
<i>is a fatal crash.</i>

844
01:13:24,199 --> 01:13:27,726
<i>We'll have more information for you</i>
<i>when it becomes available.</i>

845
01:13:29,972 --> 01:13:32,736
<i>The driver of the car, described</i>
<i>as a woman in her mid-20s...</i>

846
01:13:32,808 --> 01:13:34,776
<i>has been pronounced dead</i>
<i>at the scene.</i>

847
01:13:34,843 --> 01:13:38,370
<i>Police say it appears she lost control</i>
<i>of the light blue 1989 Mustang...</i>

848
01:13:38,447 --> 01:13:41,075
<i>and crashed through a guardrail</i>
<i>along the ravine.</i>

849
01:13:41,150 --> 01:13:44,642
<i>Investigators believe</i>
<i>she was killed upon impact--</i>

850
01:14:04,606 --> 01:14:06,733
Sir, you can't go down there.

851
01:14:06,809 --> 01:14:09,107
Sir, you can't come down here.

852
01:14:09,178 --> 01:14:11,078
- You can't go down there.
- Where is she?

853
01:14:13,982 --> 01:14:16,007
- She's gone sir. Been taken away.
- Where?

854
01:14:19,254 --> 01:14:21,518
- She's gone.
- Where?

855
01:14:21,590 --> 01:14:23,182
I'm sorry.

856
01:15:04,867 --> 01:15:06,732
<i>Hey, General,</i>
<i>how you holding up?</i>

857
01:15:06,802 --> 01:15:09,362
<i>You wouldn't believe it!</i>
<i>It's so cool.</i>

858
01:15:09,438 --> 01:15:12,669
We went swimming and climbing, and
one night there was a lightning storm.

859
01:15:12,741 --> 01:15:15,733
- <i>We had to stay in a motel!</i>
- You did?

860
01:15:15,811 --> 01:15:19,212
<i>I learned how to make campfires,</i>
<i>and there's lots of knives.</i>

861
01:15:19,281 --> 01:15:23,183
- Me and Brady can tell animal tracks.
- <i>That's terrific.</i>

862
01:15:23,252 --> 01:15:25,652
<i>I've gotta go.</i>
<i>Troop Master's calling us.</i>

863
01:15:25,721 --> 01:15:28,189
- <i>We're doing a hike!</i>
- Okay. Grant?

864
01:15:28,257 --> 01:15:30,817
I'll see you in a couple of days.
I love you.

865
01:15:30,893 --> 01:15:32,758
- I gotta go!
- <i>Grant?</i>

866
01:15:42,471 --> 01:15:45,497
It's better to tell him
when he gets back.

867
01:15:52,614 --> 01:15:54,582
Thanks for coming to get me.

868
01:15:54,650 --> 01:15:58,552
If there's anything you need...

869
01:15:58,620 --> 01:16:00,645
we're here.

870
01:16:00,722 --> 01:16:04,180
No, I won't.
I'll be fine.

871
01:16:07,195 --> 01:16:10,460
Don't let yourself... I mean, sometimes
it's better not to be alone...

872
01:16:10,532 --> 01:16:12,500
when you don't have to be.

873
01:16:12,568 --> 01:16:14,502
She was a good person.

874
01:16:16,371 --> 01:16:19,306
Kind, kind girl.

875
01:16:19,374 --> 01:16:21,103
You know, if l...

876
01:16:21,176 --> 01:16:24,168
If I haven't been myself
these past few weeks...

877
01:16:27,416 --> 01:16:29,816
I'm sorry, for everything.

878
01:16:31,119 --> 01:16:33,417
She liked you...

879
01:16:33,488 --> 01:16:35,752
and your family very much.

880
01:16:40,128 --> 01:16:43,325
We're here for you.
We really are.

881
01:17:15,897 --> 01:17:18,195
- Hello?
- <i>Michael, it's Whit.</i>

882
01:17:18,266 --> 01:17:20,598
Haven't heard back from you, man.

883
01:17:24,606 --> 01:17:26,938
My girlfriend, Brooke,
was killed Friday.

884
01:17:27,009 --> 01:17:30,809
- Oh, God. No.
- <i>Yeah.</i>

885
01:17:32,381 --> 01:17:34,315
Can I talk to you later?

886
01:17:34,383 --> 01:17:38,183
Yeah, sure, whenever.
I'm here at the office.

887
01:17:38,253 --> 01:17:39,845
Thanks.

888
01:17:56,738 --> 01:17:59,070
- Agent Carver.
- <i>Whit?</i>

889
01:17:59,141 --> 01:18:02,907
What did you mean,
you haven't heard back from me?

890
01:18:02,978 --> 01:18:06,209
<i>The message I left on Friday.</i>
<i>I understand now.</i>

891
01:18:06,281 --> 01:18:09,250
- <i>It's all right.</i>
- What message?

892
01:18:09,317 --> 01:18:11,911
<i>Well, the one about</i>
<i>speaking to your class.</i>

893
01:18:11,987 --> 01:18:17,152
I thought with some ground rules,
we could set some things straight.

894
01:18:17,225 --> 01:18:19,750
Wait, wait, wait.
You called me Friday?

895
01:18:19,828 --> 01:18:22,991
- You left a message?
- Yeah, at the house.

896
01:18:27,936 --> 01:18:30,370
When did you call?

897
01:18:30,439 --> 01:18:34,375
<i>I don't know.</i>
<i>Around 4:00 or 5:00, maybe, on Friday.</i>

898
01:18:38,847 --> 01:18:41,543
I didn't have any messages.

899
01:18:41,616 --> 01:18:44,210
<i>For Christ's sakes,</i>
<i>you just found out about Brooke.</i>

900
01:18:44,286 --> 01:18:48,552
No, I didn't have any messages.
I'll call you back.

901
01:18:57,332 --> 01:18:59,300
Whit, listen to me.

902
01:18:59,367 --> 01:19:01,892
<i>I know you can't do anything for me</i>
<i>or get me information...</i>

903
01:19:01,970 --> 01:19:03,631
but I can give you information.

904
01:19:03,705 --> 01:19:07,641
The other day when I was talking about
somebody trying to hide their history?

905
01:19:07,709 --> 01:19:11,805
I was talking about my neighbor.
Oliver Lang... that's his name.

906
01:19:11,880 --> 01:19:14,314
He used to be...

907
01:19:14,382 --> 01:19:19,081
It used to be William Fenimore. Run it
through your system, see what you got.

908
01:19:19,154 --> 01:19:21,952
- <i>Oliver Lang. You writing this down?</i>
- All right, slow down.

909
01:19:22,023 --> 01:19:24,651
This guy has a history, damn it!
Will you run the name?

910
01:19:24,726 --> 01:19:27,194
- Wait. What's he done?
- If I'm right...

911
01:19:27,262 --> 01:19:29,992
there are other people who called
my house that day, not just you.

912
01:19:30,065 --> 01:19:32,295
Find out. You can do that.
Please.

913
01:19:32,367 --> 01:19:34,927
- <i>I'll call you when I get back.</i>
- Where the hell are you going?

914
01:19:35,003 --> 01:19:36,664
To get you proof.
Run the name, Whit.

915
01:20:25,353 --> 01:20:27,287
<i>Was it hard to find me?</i>

916
01:20:28,557 --> 01:20:31,025
You've moved several times.

917
01:20:31,092 --> 01:20:34,960
Your wife said that...
Your ex-wife said...

918
01:20:35,030 --> 01:20:38,158
People know whose father I am.

919
01:20:40,669 --> 01:20:45,003
Mister, I've been through
all this before.

920
01:20:45,073 --> 01:20:47,667
The government, the police...

921
01:20:49,444 --> 01:20:51,036
and writers.

922
01:20:53,615 --> 01:20:56,345
People wanted to believe
it was political...

923
01:20:56,418 --> 01:20:59,046
some conspiracy, some group.

924
01:20:59,120 --> 01:21:02,351
Happy and I did too.

925
01:21:02,424 --> 01:21:04,619
Dean was not a strong boy.

926
01:21:04,693 --> 01:21:07,161
He was impressionable...

927
01:21:07,229 --> 01:21:10,164
believed what friends
around him said.

928
01:21:10,232 --> 01:21:13,099
Well, why couldn't he be involved...

929
01:21:13,168 --> 01:21:15,693
with people who could set him <i>up....</i>

930
01:21:15,770 --> 01:21:18,295
talk him into even this?

931
01:21:21,209 --> 01:21:25,475
The FBI, the police,
found nothing.

932
01:21:27,215 --> 01:21:32,016
It was him alone.
They decided this.

933
01:21:32,087 --> 01:21:34,078
Sixty-three dead...

934
01:21:35,557 --> 01:21:37,650
over taxes.

935
01:21:39,160 --> 01:21:40,650
Dean alone.

936
01:21:40,729 --> 01:21:43,323
You don't believe that, do you?

937
01:21:45,100 --> 01:21:47,034
I've never believed that.

938
01:21:47,102 --> 01:21:50,503
Have you heard the name
Oliver Lang or William Fenimore?

939
01:21:50,572 --> 01:21:52,506
I've heard too many names.

940
01:21:52,574 --> 01:21:56,237
Your son, Dean, was an electrician.

941
01:21:56,311 --> 01:21:59,906
Maybe he was contracted <i>for....</i>

942
01:21:59,981 --> 01:22:03,280
or he worked on a project...

943
01:22:03,351 --> 01:22:06,946
All of this
was investigated, mister!

944
01:22:07,022 --> 01:22:10,048
His neighbors, his customers...

945
01:22:10,125 --> 01:22:12,252
kids he grew up with
months ago.

946
01:22:12,327 --> 01:22:15,558
Dr. Scobee, I'm sorry
for bringing this all back.

947
01:22:15,630 --> 01:22:17,564
It never goes away.

948
01:22:17,632 --> 01:22:20,533
I had to come here.
You've got to understand.

949
01:22:20,602 --> 01:22:22,570
I think I know a man
who knew your son.

950
01:22:22,637 --> 01:22:25,606
He's 41, a structural engineer.

951
01:22:25,674 --> 01:22:28,609
He's got a wife, three kids.
He has this...

952
01:22:28,677 --> 01:22:31,475
May I ask what makes you so sure...

953
01:22:31,546 --> 01:22:34,879
that this man of yours had anything
to do with what happened here?

954
01:22:34,950 --> 01:22:38,215
For the same reason you're sure
your son didn't do it alone!

955
01:22:38,286 --> 01:22:42,814
I know my son was not alone,
because 10 children died that day!

956
01:22:42,891 --> 01:22:46,725
The day care center in the Roosevelt,
he had to know it was there.

957
01:22:46,795 --> 01:22:49,423
My son would never have done
anything to harm children.

958
01:22:49,497 --> 01:22:51,727
Your son didn't have any children.

959
01:22:51,800 --> 01:22:53,700
No!

960
01:22:53,768 --> 01:22:57,363
But he did things for them.

961
01:22:57,439 --> 01:23:00,306
He sponsored boys
from city shelters.

962
01:23:00,375 --> 01:23:05,677
Discoverer Troops. He coached
boys' football when he had time.

963
01:23:05,747 --> 01:23:08,341
Wait. Discoverer Troops?

964
01:23:10,852 --> 01:23:13,116
They're like Boy Scouts,
but for young children.

965
01:23:18,326 --> 01:23:21,159
He was a grown-up chaperon.

966
01:23:21,229 --> 01:23:26,064
He'd take them camping,
go to their meetings.

967
01:23:26,134 --> 01:23:29,797
Teach them.
There he is.

968
01:23:29,871 --> 01:23:32,601
It must have been
on some weekend adventure.

969
01:23:35,844 --> 01:23:39,109
Dean was best with children.

970
01:24:01,636 --> 01:24:03,035
Airport.

971
01:24:05,073 --> 01:24:07,598
Faraday, Grant Faraday.
I'll be there in a few hours.

972
01:24:07,675 --> 01:24:11,133
Don't let him go anywhere.
I'm coming. Tell him I'm <i>coming.</i>

973
01:24:26,828 --> 01:24:31,856
I'm here to pick up my son.
I called earlier this afternoon.

974
01:24:31,933 --> 01:24:34,060
- My son!
- What was that troop, sir?

975
01:24:34,135 --> 01:24:36,729
Troop? I don't know what troop.

976
01:24:36,805 --> 01:24:39,205
He's from Reston.
Grant Faraday.

977
01:24:41,443 --> 01:24:43,434
- Where's my son?
- Faraday.

978
01:24:44,813 --> 01:24:46,371
He was taken home
this afternoon, sir.

979
01:24:46,448 --> 01:24:48,678
- No.
- His father called.

980
01:24:48,750 --> 01:24:51,344
No, no, wait.
I'm his father. I called.

981
01:24:51,419 --> 01:24:55,253
But you called twice, sir.

982
01:24:55,323 --> 01:24:58,224
You said that there had been
an accident at home?

983
01:24:58,293 --> 01:25:00,193
- A car accident?
- No!

984
01:25:00,261 --> 01:25:02,559
You asked to speak
with his troop master, sir.

985
01:25:02,630 --> 01:25:04,621
I'm his goddamn father!
That wasn't me.

986
01:25:04,732 --> 01:25:07,200
Here it is, sir.
He was driven home.

987
01:25:07,268 --> 01:25:10,760
- By who?
- His troop master, sir.

988
01:25:13,608 --> 01:25:17,601
- He and another boy.
- What other boy?

989
01:25:17,679 --> 01:25:19,647
Lang, Brady Lang.

990
01:25:20,949 --> 01:25:24,248
The troop master left
with both of them.

991
01:27:13,561 --> 01:27:17,190
You're doing it again. I thought
I told you to come to me...

992
01:27:17,265 --> 01:27:19,199
- if there's something you wanna know.
- Where's my son?

993
01:27:19,267 --> 01:27:21,201
He's with mine. They're safe.
Can I get you something?

994
01:27:21,269 --> 01:27:23,203
- I saved his life!
- Some punch? What's that?

995
01:27:23,271 --> 01:27:25,501
- Your son, I saved his life!
- Yes, yes.

996
01:27:25,573 --> 01:27:27,768
And that's why
you're still here with us.

997
01:27:27,842 --> 01:27:30,640
- And Brooke?
- Brooke got in the way.

998
01:27:30,712 --> 01:27:33,010
We're on a schedule.
It's nothing personal.

999
01:27:33,081 --> 01:27:35,811
What the hell have you done
with my son?

1000
01:27:35,883 --> 01:27:39,842
If you want to be his father,
you'll walk to your house...

1001
01:27:39,921 --> 01:27:43,152
sleep in your bed,
teach your classes and live your life.

1002
01:27:43,224 --> 01:27:46,057
What are you telling me?
How many people are you gonna kill?

1003
01:27:46,127 --> 01:27:49,722
Well, if I see
any strange cars on my street...

1004
01:27:49,797 --> 01:27:53,130
if you feel compelled to talk
to anyone... a federal agent, perhaps...

1005
01:27:53,201 --> 01:27:56,227
then I imagine
we're just gonna kill one.

1006
01:27:56,304 --> 01:27:58,795
He's nine years old.

1007
01:27:58,873 --> 01:28:01,501
When will he be ten?

1008
01:28:04,545 --> 01:28:06,479
He's a good kid.

1009
01:28:06,547 --> 01:28:08,515
A strong kid.

1010
01:28:08,583 --> 01:28:12,576
Reminds me of a boy I grew up with.
Maybe you've heard of him.

1011
01:28:12,654 --> 01:28:16,055
Oliver Lang?

1012
01:28:16,124 --> 01:28:18,752
I found him in the woods one day.

1013
01:28:18,826 --> 01:28:21,818
I would hate for Grant
to see the same for you.

1014
01:28:21,896 --> 01:28:25,730
- You sick fuck!
- You're the sick fuck!

1015
01:28:33,574 --> 01:28:35,508
I promise you, Michael.

1016
01:28:37,845 --> 01:28:41,076
If you stay a good neighbor,
and you are a good a neighbor...

1017
01:28:43,217 --> 01:28:45,151
you'll have him back.

1018
01:28:45,219 --> 01:28:50,350
But if you don't calm down, I don't know
that I can guarantee his safety.

1019
01:28:51,993 --> 01:28:55,360
- This will all be over in a few days.
- When?

1020
01:28:55,430 --> 01:28:58,922
- You're not in any danger.
- When? Tell me.

1021
01:29:02,337 --> 01:29:03,929
Please.

1022
01:29:06,140 --> 01:29:08,438
Because of you, my son is alive.

1023
01:29:10,611 --> 01:29:13,409
I would like very much
to return the favor.

1024
01:29:16,050 --> 01:29:18,109
Now...

1025
01:29:18,186 --> 01:29:20,120
we're having a party.

1026
01:29:22,557 --> 01:29:25,651
You're more than welcome to stay.

1027
01:30:32,994 --> 01:30:35,189
You're a hard man to find.

1028
01:30:35,263 --> 01:30:37,527
What are you, uh...

1029
01:30:37,598 --> 01:30:42,501
Your assistant told me you've been
taking long walks between classes.

1030
01:30:42,570 --> 01:30:45,198
Yeah, I can't talk to you now.

1031
01:30:45,273 --> 01:30:48,071
No? Can you talk to me ever?

1032
01:30:49,944 --> 01:30:52,538
You look like shit.
What's going on?

1033
01:30:55,950 --> 01:30:59,317
- I'm here about Oliver Lang.
- I gotta get to my class.

1034
01:30:59,387 --> 01:31:02,914
Well, how about
you teach me something?

1035
01:31:02,990 --> 01:31:06,517
Oliver Lang,
formerly William Fenimore.

1036
01:31:06,594 --> 01:31:09,495
We gave him a good look
after the St. Louis thing.

1037
01:31:09,564 --> 01:31:13,091
Everybody who ever used a bomb
got a good look.

1038
01:31:13,167 --> 01:31:15,101
His name change was legal.

1039
01:31:15,169 --> 01:31:18,263
We ran his social security number
through the National Crime Center.

1040
01:31:18,339 --> 01:31:22,639
Not a mark on his record ever since.
Him and everyone he knew came up clean.

1041
01:31:27,515 --> 01:31:29,949
That's what you found out about, huh?

1042
01:31:32,153 --> 01:31:36,317
Yeah, that Wichita shit back when
he was 16 got you thinking, huh?

1043
01:31:36,390 --> 01:31:40,258
Do you have something new on him
or do you just not like him...

1044
01:31:40,328 --> 01:31:41,852
in your neighborhood?

1045
01:31:41,929 --> 01:31:46,491
'Cause if this is all you got, then
you need to stop teaching that class...

1046
01:31:46,567 --> 01:31:48,592
'cause it's gettin' inside your head.

1047
01:31:48,669 --> 01:31:52,070
You tell me you got something
to go on and I'll go...

1048
01:31:52,139 --> 01:31:55,199
but I'm not gonna walk into another
Copper Creek, and neither should you.

1049
01:31:55,276 --> 01:31:59,610
I got nothing.
I'm sorry.

1050
01:32:01,816 --> 01:32:03,750
All right. Look.

1051
01:32:06,020 --> 01:32:08,545
I ran those phone records,
like you asked.

1052
01:32:08,623 --> 01:32:11,751
Could've meant my job,
but I did it.

1053
01:32:11,826 --> 01:32:14,158
Two telephone calls that Friday...
one from me...

1054
01:32:14,228 --> 01:32:18,289
and another from a pay phone
out Route 180, Pine Glenn Outlets.

1055
01:32:18,366 --> 01:32:19,697
Pine Glenn?

1056
01:32:21,002 --> 01:32:24,494
A telephone call from your neighbor.
Nothing.

1057
01:32:30,912 --> 01:32:32,846
Talk to me, Michael.

1058
01:32:34,215 --> 01:32:36,149
What's going on?

1059
01:32:38,452 --> 01:32:40,386
Talk to me.

1060
01:32:48,329 --> 01:32:50,263
Give up the goddamn class.

1061
01:32:56,938 --> 01:32:59,304
I'd like to rent a car
tomorrow morning.

1062
01:32:59,373 --> 01:33:01,739
How early could I pick that up?

1063
01:33:04,378 --> 01:33:06,312
<i>Michael Faraday.</i>

1064
01:33:49,657 --> 01:33:51,056
Oliver Lang, please.

1065
01:33:51,125 --> 01:33:53,525
<i>Mr. Lang is out of the office.</i>
<i>Would you like to leave a message?</i>

1066
01:33:53,594 --> 01:33:55,585
I need to reach him.
This is a business emergency.

1067
01:33:55,663 --> 01:33:58,894
<i>Mr. Lang isn't expected in this morning.</i>

1068
01:33:58,966 --> 01:34:01,366
- I'll call back. Thanks.
- <i>Is there something else...</i>

1069
01:34:01,435 --> 01:34:03,630
No.

1070
01:37:56,670 --> 01:38:01,130
Hey, neighbor, you all right?
What you doin' on this side of town?

1071
01:38:04,078 --> 01:38:06,546
Had to know, didn't ya?
Had to know.

1072
01:38:06,614 --> 01:38:09,174
Couldn't leave your neighbor alone.

1073
01:38:24,164 --> 01:38:26,189
Didn't you check up on me?

1074
01:38:26,267 --> 01:38:28,292
Didn't you?

1075
01:38:28,369 --> 01:38:30,963
Did you really think
we'd leave anything to chance?

1076
01:38:31,038 --> 01:38:33,472
<i>Fifty-one.</i>

1077
01:38:33,540 --> 01:38:36,771
I've got your shadow.
Go ahead. We're still on schedule.

1078
01:38:40,514 --> 01:38:43,244
- You gonna miss your son, Michael?
- Please.

1079
01:38:43,317 --> 01:38:46,343
You've given me no choice!

1080
01:38:46,420 --> 01:38:50,356
You think I wanted this?
I told you you were gonna get him back!

1081
01:38:50,424 --> 01:38:53,860
How am I gonna do that now?
How am I gonna trust you now?

1082
01:38:53,928 --> 01:38:56,920
Where are you taking him?
Where's the bomb?

1083
01:39:00,200 --> 01:39:03,692
I'm a messenger, Michael.
I'm a messenger!

1084
01:39:03,771 --> 01:39:06,205
There's millions of us,
waiting to take up arms...

1085
01:39:06,273 --> 01:39:08,468
ready to spread the word.

1086
01:39:08,542 --> 01:39:09,873
Millions of us!

1087
01:39:09,944 --> 01:39:12,139
The government's
not who you're killing!

1088
01:39:12,212 --> 01:39:15,613
Yes, yes, they'll pay.
They'll pay for their sins...

1089
01:39:15,683 --> 01:39:17,480
- You're killing children!
- Their lies, their children.

1090
01:39:17,551 --> 01:39:19,280
- Children die!
- This is war.

1091
01:39:19,353 --> 01:39:21,548
In a war, children die.

1092
01:39:21,622 --> 01:39:23,817
- You're with us!
- No!

1093
01:39:46,647 --> 01:39:49,514
<i>Liberty Two, status.</i>

1094
01:39:50,851 --> 01:39:52,512
<i>Status one, go.</i>

1095
01:39:52,586 --> 01:39:55,680
That's what you stand for.

1096
01:39:55,756 --> 01:39:59,123
You tell them you stand for
blowing up families...

1097
01:39:59,193 --> 01:40:01,127
for orphan sons.

1098
01:40:02,896 --> 01:40:06,525
Your father really kill himself,
you son of a bitch?

1099
01:40:06,600 --> 01:40:08,693
Or is that just one of your
goddamn stories?

1100
01:40:10,270 --> 01:40:13,671
- Call it off!
- It's for you, Michael.

1101
01:40:13,741 --> 01:40:15,800
- It's for all of us.
- It's not for me. Call it off!

1102
01:40:16,944 --> 01:40:19,936
Are you happy in your godless,
suburban life?

1103
01:40:20,014 --> 01:40:22,380
Call off the bomb!

1104
01:40:22,449 --> 01:40:25,282
Call off the fuckin' bomb!

1105
01:40:29,189 --> 01:40:31,316
They sent your wife
to her death.

1106
01:40:31,392 --> 01:40:34,361
Surely you won't be sorry
to see them go.

1107
01:40:41,635 --> 01:40:43,227
You're too late!

1108
01:41:16,603 --> 01:41:18,594
Let's get it done.

1109
01:41:28,816 --> 01:41:30,215
- Agent Carver.
- <i>Listen to me.</i>

1110
01:41:30,284 --> 01:41:34,345
There's a bomb on its way
to your offices. Get everybody out!

1111
01:41:34,421 --> 01:41:36,616
- What's going on?
- <i>It's in a white van.</i>

1112
01:41:36,690 --> 01:41:39,022
A Liberty Delivery Van.
Grant's in there.

1113
01:41:41,595 --> 01:41:43,529
They want the FBI this time!

1114
01:41:43,597 --> 01:41:45,963
Michael, you're breaking up!

1115
01:41:47,367 --> 01:41:49,733
Whit? Shit!

1116
01:41:54,508 --> 01:41:56,806
Come on!

1117
01:42:09,790 --> 01:42:11,485
Security, main gate.

1118
01:43:03,544 --> 01:43:05,273
Out of the way!

1119
01:43:57,097 --> 01:43:59,361
That's the van!

1120
01:43:59,433 --> 01:44:01,924
Stop it!

1121
01:44:06,173 --> 01:44:08,903
- Stop the van!
- Sir, step out of the vehicle!

1122
01:44:08,976 --> 01:44:12,742
- There's a bomb in the van!
- Step out of the vehicle!

1123
01:44:12,813 --> 01:44:15,281
- It's got a goddamn bomb!
- Michael, wait!

1124
01:44:15,349 --> 01:44:18,512
That's the van!
There's a bomb in there!

1125
01:44:18,585 --> 01:44:21,611
- That van was authorized.
- That's the van! Grant's inside!

1126
01:44:21,688 --> 01:44:24,122
It's the noon delivery.

1127
01:44:26,360 --> 01:44:28,624
Grant's in there!
It's got a goddamn bomb!

1128
01:44:38,338 --> 01:44:39,805
Hold your fire!

1129
01:44:55,422 --> 01:44:58,914
- Don't shoot!
- In the van!

1130
01:45:02,629 --> 01:45:06,258
Get everyone out of the building!
There's a bomb in the van!

1131
01:45:12,639 --> 01:45:15,608
- Get him out of the building.
- Check the goddamn van.

1132
01:45:18,679 --> 01:45:21,147
We gotta get everybody out of here.
There's a bomb.

1133
01:45:21,214 --> 01:45:23,148
- It's in there.
- Easy.

1134
01:45:26,520 --> 01:45:27,987
Wait! That's...

1135
01:45:28,055 --> 01:45:30,819
That's not the man.

1136
01:45:30,891 --> 01:45:33,257
- All right.
- Grant!

1137
01:45:34,795 --> 01:45:36,262
Let him go.

1138
01:45:36,330 --> 01:45:38,594
I said, let him go!

1139
01:45:39,599 --> 01:45:42,124
- Back off!
- The van's clean.

1140
01:45:42,202 --> 01:45:44,796
There's nothing in here.

1141
01:45:44,871 --> 01:45:47,806
Go ahead, Michael.

1142
01:46:00,954 --> 01:46:03,354
Michael, it's all clear.

1143
01:46:03,423 --> 01:46:06,290
The guy's authorized to be here.

1144
01:46:06,360 --> 01:46:10,524
We're all authorized to be here.
Everyone except you.

1145
01:46:13,734 --> 01:46:16,794
All right? Come on.

1146
01:46:22,142 --> 01:46:24,337
It's all right.

1147
01:46:39,793 --> 01:46:41,226
Hey, guys!

1148
01:47:00,514 --> 01:47:02,072
Stand by.

1149
01:47:38,618 --> 01:47:40,848
<i>Everyone except you.</i>

1150
01:47:53,533 --> 01:47:54,966
Boom.

1151
01:48:29,436 --> 01:48:32,269
<i>Right now, I'm sort of breathless.</i>

1152
01:48:32,339 --> 01:48:34,773
<i>I've just gotten here,</i>
<i>and there are people lying...</i>

1153
01:48:54,261 --> 01:48:56,729
<i>It looks just like a war zone!</i>

1154
01:49:09,876 --> 01:49:12,572
<i>Officials at this point believe</i>
<i>a bomb went off.</i>

1155
01:49:12,646 --> 01:49:15,206
<i>They're not sure</i>
<i>which floor, how big.</i>

1156
01:49:15,282 --> 01:49:19,844
<i>Obviously, it was massive</i>
<i>to create the kind of devastation...</i>

1157
01:49:54,220 --> 01:49:56,586
<i>Preliminary reports indicate</i>
<i>the bombing was the work...</i>

1158
01:49:56,656 --> 01:50:00,251
<i>of this man, Michael Faraday</i>
<i>of Reston, Virginia.</i>

1159
01:50:00,327 --> 01:50:03,421
<i>A professor of history</i>
<i>at George Washington University...</i>

1160
01:50:03,496 --> 01:50:07,296
<i>Officials will not confirm reports</i>
<i>that the bombing had anything to do....</i>

1161
01:50:07,367 --> 01:50:11,701
<i>with the death of Mr. Faraday's wife,</i>
<i>who had been an FBI agent.</i>

1162
01:50:19,412 --> 01:50:21,846
<i>Students and colleagues both say...</i>

1163
01:50:21,915 --> 01:50:26,409
<i>that Faraday's behavior was increasingly</i>
<i>erratic in the weeks leading</i> up...

1164
01:50:26,486 --> 01:50:30,047
<i>He was really intense, you know?</i>
<i>Knew all about these terrorists...</i>

1165
01:50:30,123 --> 01:50:32,250
<i>how they worked, what they wanted.</i>

1166
01:50:32,325 --> 01:50:35,158
<i>He was really into it.</i>
<i>It was my favorite class.</i>

1167
01:50:35,228 --> 01:50:38,288
<i>We went to this field trip once.</i>
<i>It was Copper Creek.</i>

1168
01:50:38,365 --> 01:50:42,529
<i>He practically broke down and started</i>
<i>crying, something about his wife.</i>

1169
01:50:42,602 --> 01:50:45,765
<i>We all sort of knew about it, but</i>
<i>he never really wanted to talk about it.</i>

1170
01:50:47,974 --> 01:50:51,603
<i>Faraday reportedly blamed the Bureau</i>
<i>for its role in his wife's death...</i>

1171
01:50:51,678 --> 01:50:53,270
<i>almost three years ago.</i>

1172
01:50:53,346 --> 01:50:55,439
<i>Specifically, sources</i>
<i>speculate his target....</i>

1173
01:50:55,515 --> 01:51:00,680
<i>may have been Agent Whit Carver, one of</i>
<i>the 184 people to perish in the attack.</i>

1174
01:51:00,754 --> 01:51:04,019
<i>Carver was a partner</i>
<i>of Faraday's wife at Copper Creek....</i>

1175
01:51:04,090 --> 01:51:06,251
<i>and Faraday</i>
<i>may have held him responsible.</i>

1176
01:51:06,326 --> 01:51:10,353
<i>All I know is what he told me</i>
<i>in his office one day after class.</i>

1177
01:51:10,430 --> 01:51:12,921
<i>I'll never forget that.</i>

1178
01:51:12,999 --> 01:51:16,162
<i>He said, "Sweetheart...</i>

1179
01:51:16,236 --> 01:51:19,433
<i>one day those men are going to pay.</i>

